SAFETY & PRIVACY
- The site must explicitly state in the footer and in chat UI that Algebrix will never request user account credentials and will not perform any purchase or login actions.
- Rate limit agent runs to avoid abuse (e.g., max 2 concurrent agent tasks per IP; the backend should enforce this).

FINAL NOTE
- Provide a complete ZIP-ready project output and a single-page `README.md` that a user can paste into Replit, set the env var, run `npm install` and `npm run dev`, and see a working landing page and chat with basic agent functionality.
- If any steps fail due to environment constraints (e.g., Playwright not supported), add a clear fallback plan as described above.

